OL,3,CHow a building once called 'Britain's
OL,4,Cugliest' is now officially protected
OL,6,FA 35-year battle over London's
OL,7,Fbrutalist Southbank Centre has finally
OL,8,Fbeen resolved after the building, once
OL,9,Fdescribed as Britain's ugliest, was
OL,10,Fofficially recognised as being of
OL,11,Fspecial architectural interest.
OL,13,FThe site has been granted Grade II
OL,14,Flisted status which means the 1960s
OL,15,Fstructure will be protected from
OL,16,Fdemolition and face strict rules
OL,17,Faround any alterations.
