OL,3,CHow a building once called 'Britain's
OL,4,Cugliest' is now officially protected
OL,6,FBut the buildings divide opinion
OL,7,Fbetween those who think they are an
OL,8,Fimportant surviving example of British
OL,9,FBrutalist architecture and those who
OL,10,Fbelieve the concrete designs are bleak
OL,11,Fand oppressive.
OL,13,F"The Grade II listing recognises the
OL,14,Farchitectural and civic importance of
OL,15,Fthe Queen Elizabeth Hall and Hayward
OL,16,FGallery," the Southbank Centre said.
OL,18,F"The listing underlines the need for
OL,19,FGovernment investment in our buildings
OL,20,F- all of which they own.
